message.content: If Sally has 3 brothers and her brothers have 2 sisters each, then she would have a total of 3 brothers x 2 sisters = 6 sisters. However, this question seems to be a trick question because it is not possible for Sally to have more sisters than herself if we assume that "her" refers to Sally in the second sentence. In this case, there are no additional sisters mentioned or implied beyond Sally. Therefore, Sally has 0 sisters, as she is the only female sibling in the family.
